1
00:00:37,119 --> 00:00:37,920
And besides,

2
00:00:42,119 --> 00:00:43,600
around our neighborhood,

3
00:00:43,719 --> 00:00:47,520
there are century-old high-quality wells.

4
00:00:48,119 --> 00:00:50,439
It'd be a waste not to make vinegar.

5
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:52,479
Life should be lived to the fullest.

6
00:00:53,039 --> 00:00:56,280
We can't let Second Aunt's vinegar workshop go to waste.

7
00:00:56,759 --> 00:00:59,320
This is exactly what we should be doing.

8
00:00:59,719 --> 00:01:00,560
Let's get to work!

9
00:01:01,799 --> 00:01:02,600
Right!

10
00:01:03,439 --> 00:01:05,560
We must be positive in life.

11
00:01:06,159 --> 00:01:07,159
Work hard!

12
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:08,599
Let's do it together!

13
00:01:10,239 --> 00:01:10,799
Second Brother.

14
00:01:11,239 --> 00:01:11,879
Let's get started!

15
00:01:54,319 --> 00:01:55,239
You're awake?

16
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:58,000
You really can't hold your liquor.

17
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,519
You're not even as good as me, a woman.

18
00:02:05,079 --> 00:02:06,120
Don't look at me.

19
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,200
I didn't agree to anything.

20
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:09,280
I'm just being forced to work.

21
00:02:13,199 --> 00:02:14,159
What are you guys doing?

22
00:02:14,719 --> 00:02:15,439
Setting up the vinegar workshop.

23
00:02:15,639 --> 00:02:16,879
Didn't we talk about this last night?

24
00:02:24,599 --> 00:02:25,919
We can't run a vinegar workshop.

25
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,159
Last night you also said

26
00:02:28,159 --> 00:02:30,039
we need to be serious, ambitious, and proactive.

27
00:02:30,439 --> 00:02:32,319
How did you change your mind after sleeping on it?

28
00:02:33,039 --> 00:02:34,919
Besides, I've already asked around.

29
00:02:34,919 --> 00:02:36,639
There are sole proprietors doing business now.

30
00:02:37,479 --> 00:02:37,960
Yes,

31
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,280
things are different now than before.

32
00:02:40,479 --> 00:02:41,240
But that doesn't mean

33
00:02:41,439 --> 00:02:43,240
there isn't any risk right now.

34
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,319
I said we're doing it, so we're doing it.

35
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:46,759
I'm in.

36
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:54,520
You have to look at the trends.

37
00:02:54,639 --> 00:02:57,120
Since things are changing, they'll keep changing.

38
00:02:57,319 --> 00:02:58,840
If we seize the opportunity first,

39
00:02:58,879 --> 00:03:00,680
we'll be the trendsetters of the times.

40
00:03:01,879 --> 00:03:03,479
That's a new term.

41
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,039
I'm timid.

42
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,000
I'm not doing it.

43
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:12,240
But you helped me with that batch of vinegar last time.

44
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:13,680
You were involved too.

45
00:03:14,639 --> 00:03:16,120
I simply thought

46
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,759
you wanted to sell off the finished vinegar.

47
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,520
Now you want to run a vinegar workshop

48
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:20,639
and sell vinegar.

49
00:03:21,199 --> 00:03:22,199
Is that the same thing?

50
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,400
Is there any difference?

51
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,840
When I tried fishing and pig farming before,

52
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,520
I was too impulsive.

53
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,000
But,

54
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,080
we have an advantage in running a vinegar workshop now.

55
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:39,319
Second Aunt's workshop is ready-made.

56
00:03:39,599 --> 00:03:40,840
The brewing tools are there,

57
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:42,080
and we have the brewing method too.

58
00:03:42,479 --> 00:03:43,879
It's a clear money-making opportunity,

59
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,240
so why shouldn't we do it?

60
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:46,800
I'll say it again.

61
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,199
Given the climate, everyone is still waiting and seeing.

62
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:51,080
And vinegar brewing requires high skill.

63
00:03:51,319 --> 00:03:52,199
You haven't prepared anything.

64
00:03:52,199 --> 00:03:53,000
How can you start?

65
00:03:55,319 --> 00:03:56,120
You're just messing around.

66
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:57,240
Haiyang,

67
00:03:57,919 --> 00:03:58,520
Xiaochuan,

68
00:03:58,879 --> 00:03:59,800
come back with me.

69
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:01,960
Zheng Minjiang!

70
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,759
Opportunities don't last forever.

71
00:04:05,599 --> 00:04:06,199
Let's go.

72
00:04:10,479 --> 00:04:11,639
You're willing to miss out,

73
00:04:11,639 --> 00:04:13,919
but are you going to make your brothers miss out too?

74
00:04:17,639 --> 00:04:18,600
I refuse to believe

75
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:20,240
that something I'm determined to do,

76
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,000
I can't accomplish.

77
00:04:22,279 --> 00:04:23,120
I'll do it myself!

78
00:04:42,639 --> 00:04:44,439
The motorcycle only sold for three hundred?

79
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:46,439
You think just because your mom is old,

80
00:04:46,439 --> 00:04:47,480
she doesn't know anything?

81
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:49,360
Where did you hide the rest of the money?

82
00:04:49,639 --> 00:04:50,439
Hand it over to me.

83
00:04:50,879 --> 00:04:52,480
I'm saving that money to do business.

84
00:04:52,879 --> 00:04:53,600
These three hundred yuan

85
00:04:53,759 --> 00:04:55,360
are enough for our family to use for a while.

86
00:04:55,639 --> 00:04:56,759
I told you,

87
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,439
you need to look out for your little sister.

88
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:00,319
Yingtang is still a student.

89
00:05:00,519 --> 00:05:02,120
What reason does she have to spend so much money?

90
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:03,160
Mom,

91
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:05,399
it's wrong for you to spoil Yingtang like this.

92
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:06,879
I'm asking you,

93
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,040
the rest of that money,

94
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,279
are you giving it to me or not?

95
00:05:09,519 --> 00:05:10,319
No.

96
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:12,560
What are you doing?

97
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,959
Mom, why do you treat Yingrong like that?

98
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:20,519
So what?

99
00:05:20,759 --> 00:05:22,720
You old ones and young ones are turning the house upside down!

100
00:05:22,879 --> 00:05:24,600
Shouldn't the big money stay in the family?

101
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,040
Which family?

102
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,720
I gave birth to such a selfish child.

103
00:05:29,439 --> 00:05:30,879
I'll say something unpleasant,

104
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:31,720
looking at the way she is,

105
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:32,519
when we get old later,

106
00:05:32,519 --> 00:05:34,040
she'll still need her little sister to support her.

107
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:35,879
Yingtang is still a student.

108
00:05:36,399 --> 00:05:37,920
She shouldn't be spending so much money.

109
00:05:38,199 --> 00:05:39,079
In this house,

110
00:05:39,319 --> 00:05:40,600
she's the one who spends the most.

111
00:05:41,519 --> 00:05:42,480
She doesn't earn money,

112
00:05:43,199 --> 00:05:43,720
so

113
00:05:43,959 --> 00:05:45,120
she doesn't feel the pinch when spending.

114
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:46,680
I think Yingrong...

115
00:05:46,959 --> 00:05:47,920
what she said is right.

116
00:05:48,519 --> 00:05:49,800
Yingrong says, Yingrong says...

117
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:50,800
Yingrong says crap.

118
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:52,720
Look at her state,

119
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:54,040
she doesn't even have a job.

120
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:55,720
Can we even count on her?

121
00:05:56,279 --> 00:05:57,959
Yingzhu is a pushover.

122
00:05:58,319 --> 00:05:59,879
She just gets bullied by her in-laws.

123
00:06:00,319 --> 00:06:01,360
Only Yingtang...

124
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:02,879
when we get old,

125
00:06:03,079 --> 00:06:04,279
we'll have to rely on her to take care of us.

126
00:06:04,519 --> 00:06:05,480
Rely on her or not,

127
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:06,879
that's a matter for the future.

128
00:06:07,439 --> 00:06:08,399
These three kids

129
00:06:08,759 --> 00:06:09,839
are all our own flesh and blood.

130
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,839
We need to treat them equally.

131
00:06:12,439 --> 00:06:13,920
I can't treat them equally.

132
00:06:14,279 --> 00:06:15,360
If you really want to be good to her,

133
00:06:15,519 --> 00:06:16,680
urge her to get married sooner.

134
00:06:17,519 --> 00:06:18,439
I've always felt

135
00:06:18,839 --> 00:06:20,000
that Yingtang has been spoiled by you

136
00:06:20,199 --> 00:06:21,079
beyond all limits.

137
00:06:21,279 --> 00:06:22,360
It's going to cause trouble.

138
00:06:22,519 --> 00:06:23,480
I want to spoil her.

139
00:06:23,639 --> 00:06:24,279
So what?

140
00:06:38,879 --> 00:06:39,480
Sis,

141
00:06:40,519 --> 00:06:42,519
I saw you didn't eat dinner.

142
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:44,600
Eat this bowl of jelly noodles.

143
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:47,240
I'm not hungry.

144
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:49,279
Where's Bao'er?

145
00:06:50,279 --> 00:06:51,800
Mom is watching him.

146
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,360
Don't be mad at Mom.

147
00:07:02,839 --> 00:07:04,319
I just don't understand.

148
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,319
Why doesn't she like me?

149
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:08,319
She favors the youngest.

150
00:07:08,319 --> 00:07:09,399
She dotes on the youngest.

151
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:11,800
Why does she just find me so objectionable?

152
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:13,720
Am I not her biological daughter?

153
00:07:16,279 --> 00:07:17,319
When I was little,

154
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,720
I thought if I studied hard,

155
00:07:19,879 --> 00:07:21,360
she would definitely like me.

156
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:22,519
Later,

157
00:07:23,279 --> 00:07:25,600
I thought, I need to work hard to earn a lot of money,

158
00:07:25,839 --> 00:07:27,519
then she would surely like me.

159
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:29,680
And then later,

160
00:07:30,439 --> 00:07:33,000
I thought, I need to work hard,

161
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,800
then she would surely like me.

162
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:38,680
But no matter what I do,

163
00:07:39,879 --> 00:07:41,040
as soon as there's a problem,

164
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,639
it's always my fault.

165
00:07:43,199 --> 00:07:44,319
I don't understand.

166
00:07:45,199 --> 00:07:47,560
Why is it always my fault?

167
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:00,120
But I don't care anymore.

168
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,160
I have a goal now.

169
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,800
I must make Baliang Vinegar a success.

170
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:05,720
When that happens,

171
00:08:05,839 --> 00:08:07,279
I'll leave this family for good.

172
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:14,879
What are you doing?

173
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,000
Sis, go to sleep.

174
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,600
I'm going to the yard for some quiet.

175
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:23,439
Number Two.

176
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:24,639
Where are you going?

177
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:25,879
To earn money to pay off debts.

178
00:08:26,279 --> 00:08:27,240
You found a job?

179
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,480
Where is it?

180
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,279
My Number Two...

181
00:08:36,879 --> 00:08:38,279
has found a job.

182
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:41,279
Mom, you took my money.

183
00:08:41,279 --> 00:08:43,159
I gave birth to you, so what's yours is mine.

184
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:44,240
So what if I took it?

185
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,840
If you don't give it back, I won't come home.

186
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,799
Yingrong, don't go.

187
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:53,919
You...

188
00:08:54,519 --> 00:08:55,480
Don't be mad at Mom.

189
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:57,120
I got the money back for you.

190
00:08:58,519 --> 00:08:59,559
I know.

191
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:01,320
You've been wronged this time.

192
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:04,399
But whatever you do in the future,

193
00:09:05,039 --> 00:09:06,120
I will support you.

194
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,240
Sis.

195
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,240
I can't help you much.

196
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:20,679
But what I can help with,

197
00:09:21,279 --> 00:09:22,440
I definitely will.

198
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:30,600
Sis.

199
00:09:31,639 --> 00:09:32,480
I'm leaving now.

200
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:38,759
Wang Yingrong!

201
00:09:40,639 --> 00:09:41,759
Wang Yingrong!

202
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,039
Go, quickly.

203
00:09:43,519 --> 00:09:44,519
You lie to everyone.

204
00:09:44,519 --> 00:09:45,039
Mom!

205
00:09:45,039 --> 00:09:46,000
You just lie to your mom.

206
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:48,159
How did this money turn into paper?

207
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:49,519
Get the money back for me!

208
00:09:49,879 --> 00:09:50,679
Mom.

209
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,480
This was Yingrong's money to begin with.

210
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:54,279
She should give this money to the family.

211
00:09:54,279 --> 00:09:55,919
Look at what you've done.

212
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,440
Alright, Mom.

213
00:09:57,879 --> 00:09:58,799
I'm so furious.

214
00:09:58,919 --> 00:09:59,720
Alright, stop being angry.

215
00:10:06,279 --> 00:10:06,960
Mom.

216
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:11,840
Why did it take you so long to bring the money?

217
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,000
Right now at the factory,

218
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:16,120
they only give basic living expenses each month.

219
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:17,519
The family doesn't have much money left.

220
00:10:17,519 --> 00:10:19,279
Youngest, you need to be frugal.

221
00:10:21,919 --> 00:10:23,120
Just this little bit?

222
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,279
Didn't Second Sister have a motorcycle to sell?

223
00:10:25,919 --> 00:10:28,039
She hid the money from the sale.

224
00:10:28,879 --> 00:10:29,360
Mom.

225
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:30,320
To be respected by others,

226
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:31,720
isn't that easy.

227
00:10:32,799 --> 00:10:33,799
You only give this much money,

228
00:10:33,799 --> 00:10:34,840
it's not even enough to buy one piece of clothing.

229
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:36,960
And you said you'd let me stay in the city.

230
00:10:37,559 --> 00:10:38,320
And don't come here all the time.

231
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:40,480
If others see you,

232
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:41,840
they'll think our family is so poor.

233
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:46,240
I know it's not easy for you.

234
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,440
Mom will bring you the money as soon as possible.

235
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:49,720
Just wait.

236
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:52,840
My poor Youngest.

237
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:57,039
No, I can't drink anymore.

238
00:10:57,039 --> 00:10:58,799
I have the preliminary entrance exam tomorrow.

239
00:10:58,799 --> 00:11:00,240
I really can't drink anymore.

240
00:11:10,799 --> 00:11:12,120
If you drink this wine,

241
00:11:12,759 --> 00:11:13,679
the money is yours.

242
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,159
Really?

243
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:37,279
Keep going.

244
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,200
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

245
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:45,639
Drink, drink, drink!

246
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:51,759
Can you handle it?

247
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:53,519
Hello?

248
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:54,639
Hello?

249
00:12:45,399 --> 00:12:45,919
Yingtang.

250
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,519
Why didn't you come to the preliminary entrance exam?

251
00:12:47,799 --> 00:12:48,399
If you don't take the preliminary exam,

252
00:12:48,399 --> 00:12:50,120
you won't have a chance to take the college entrance exam.

253
00:12:54,879 --> 00:12:55,519
That's right.

254
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:58,600
I won't be able to take the college entrance exam.

255
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:04,519
Then what did I study these three years for?
